\subsection{Lifshitz algebra}
\label{sec:Lifshitz}


In the previous Sections, we saw that the presence of boosts complicates considerably the situation, since a number of structures transforms in a non-covariant way under them. Here we investigate another type of non-relativistic space-time symmetry, the Lifshitz algebra,  which can be obtained from the Galilei one by discarding the boosts. By doing so, the presence of the $U (1)$ symmetry associated with the central extension becomes unnecessary, since it decouples from the space-time generators and turns into an internal symmetry.


Now, all the structures can be classified in terms of irreducible representations of the $\mathfrak{so}(n-1)$ algebra of spatial rotations. The corresponding transformation properties of the fields can be read from Tables~\ref{gfield_trans_1} and~\ref{gfield_trans_2}, as well as from the equations~\eqref{scaling_gauge} and~\eqref{scaling_strength}. For the Lifshitz algebra,  $n_{{\mu}{\nu}}$, ${\theta}^{ij}_{{\mu}{\nu}}$ and $W_{{\mu}{\nu}}$ are identical to the ones in~\eqref{mod_field_str}, whereas the spatial torsion reads

text:
